Package soot

Class SootMethod

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.tagkit.AbstractHost
      • soot.SootMethod
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ClassMember, MethodOrMethodContext, SootMethodInterface, Host
    public class SootMethod
extends AbstractHost
implements ClassMember, MethodOrMethodContext, SootMethodInterface
    Soot representation of a Java method. Can be declared to belong to a SootClass. Does not contain the actual code, which belongs to a Body. The getActiveBody() method points to the currently-active body.

      • retrieveActiveBody

        public Body retrieveActiveBody()
        Returns the active body if present, else constructs an active body and returns that. If you called Scene.v().loadClassAndSupport() for a class yourself, it will not be an application class, so you cannot get retrieve its active body. Please call SootClass.setApplicationClass() on the relevant class.

      • retrieveActiveBody

        public Body retrieveActiveBody​(Consumer<Body> consumer)
        Returns the active body if present, else constructs an active body, calls the consumer and returns the body afterward. If you called Scene.v().loadClassAndSupport() for a class yourself, it will not be an application class, so you cannot get retrieve its active body. Please call SootClass.setApplicationClass() on the relevant class.
        Parameters:
        consumer - Consumer that takes in the body of the method. The consumer is only invoked if the current invocation constructs a new body and is guaranteed to terminate before the body is available to other threads.
        Returns:
        active body of the method
